answers.answer: Your doctor is still gonna want you to do it.

No problem.  Just call your dr. Office and request a new paper to take to the lab. Of course they will still want you to take it :) where I live the papers are good for 6 months. Probably because they know pregnancy can make us very forgetful.  I was supposed to go have mine tomorrow but unfortunately I am losing the baby :/ but best of luck to you! Hope for good test results mama!

K good lol and I know I forget everything!!! And im sooo sorry for your loss, I lost my son January and it was the hardest thing, no parent should ever loose a child. Theres nothing I can say to ease the pain but I hope you feel better soon xo
That's very normal :) and I'm sorry for your loss as well. Thanks for your kind words and I'm happy to hear you have been able to get pregnant again following your loss <3
